The paper proposes a novel approach for maritime anomaly detection using deep learning techniques, specifically variational recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a contrario detection, which is a statistical method for detecting anomalies, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks for capturing complex patterns in vessel behavior, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or signal processing (cs.SI).
